   <indicator ascending="0" measure="1">
    <title>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Output Indicator</narrative>
    </title>
    <description>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Number of guidance notes on gender analysis across all sectors of the NDCs, to better identify, understand, and describe relevance of gender differences for climate policies.
- Analysis of the industry and construction sectors as priority sectors for NDCs to assess the impact of climate change on the sector and identify the specific actions for mitigation. 
- Analysis of the transport and infrastructure sectors as priority sectors for NDCs to assess the impact of climate change on the sector and identify the specific actions for mitigation and/or adaptation. 
- Gender analysis of all draft sectoral NDCs (including water, energy, agriculture, biodiversity and ecosystems), to better describe relevance of gender differences for climate policies and to facilitate empowerment of women, youth, and other vulnerable groups to be more actively engaged in climate action.
- Stakeholder consultations conducted on NDC revision, with government and non-government stakeholders, focusing on industry and transport sectors, as well as on gender mainstreaming.
- The 5-year or 10-year plan (timelines to be agreed with governmental stakeholders) for NDCs implementation with prioritization of specific actions to be undertaken in the near and long-term.
- Three (3) position papers for UNDP-led policy work in support of the climate action in Tajikistan, a) clearly defining UNDP&#x2019;s offer and value addition, as well as b) theories of change for proposed areas of support.</narrative>
    </description>
